editorialNotes.standard: Ski Safari returns with an all-new look and the same addictive gameplay. To outrun an impending avalanche youâll need to crash through cabins, team up with Yetis and eagles and perform tons of tricks. The gameplay is as fast-paced as ever, and a fresh multiplayer mode and colourful new worlds to explore (like a prehistoric volcano) will keep you cruising down these mountains for a long time.

editorialNotes.standard: You might get stuck the first time you play Gorogoa. But once the gears of your brain settle into the right configurations, youâll see how smart this mix of art and perspective really is. Layers pile upon layers, doors transport you between realities, strange creatures and wild environments blend together into a fascinating interactive collage youâll want to peel apart to discover what lies underneath.

Zipping down snowy hills, trying to stay ahead of a massive avalancheâthe pressureâs always on in this infinite-racing classic. And we love that whirlwind pace, fuelled by landing backflips and hitching rides on penguins, snowmobiles and yetis. From the gameâs masterful one-touch controls to its cheery music, every aspect feels perfectly tuned to keep you playing through long afternoons and late nights.

With endless solutions to every challenge, itâs a stylish, supremely satisfying test of your creativity and puzzle-solving prowess.

editorialNotes.standard: At a glance, hocus doesnât look very complicated. You swipe to move a red cube along a latticework of plain grey beams. But donât let the minimalist visuals fool youâthe gameâs intelligent, abstract puzzles force you to look at things in a new way, like a cubist translation of Monument Valley. As you progress, the levels quickly get complex. But the peaceful music and crisp design make spending time in its world a richly rewarding experience.

A rare kind of triumph, Prune takes a simple ideaâpruning treesâand shapes it into a creative, deeply playable puzzle game. The visuals echo the style of Japanese painting in striking fashion, and the beautiful music instills a contemplative tone as you swipe to trim the limbs of a rapidly growing tree and guide it around obstacles. Thereâs no frantic pace, no demanding skills to masterâonly a quietly bewitching and unforgettable experience.
editorialNotes.short: A contemplative and creative experience - trimming trees has never been so beautiful.

editorialNotes.standard: What secrets lie in the shadows of this Apple Design Awardâwinning puzzler? Soothing ambient music and thematic backdrops make completing each challenge as much meditation as entertainmentâwhile timers and achievements give each level a competitive feel.
editorialNotes.short: With stunning visuals and satisfying solutions, this game is one to savour.
